It's understood the lions were poisoned yesterday before their paws, snouts and jaws were hacked off. JOHANNESBURG - North West police are investigating a case of illegal hunting after eight captive-bred lions were killed on a farm in Swartruggens. It's understood the lions were poisoned yesterday before their paws, snouts and jaws were hacked off. The police's Sabata Mokgwabone said a case of illegal hunting has been opened at the Koster police station